President Obama has announced the appointment of a Presidential Delegation to attend the inauguration of President Juan Manuel Santos of Colombia. The delegation will be led by Thomas A. Shannon, Jr., Counselor of the Department of State, and will include Kevin Whitaker, U.S. Ambassador to Colombia, and Ramona E. Romero, General Counsel of the U.S. Department of Agriculture. The inauguration will take place on August 7, 2014.